 whether I can add a test class in the com.ibm.flyway package. I can create a Java test file named ClassPathScannerTest.java, and it can be public within that package. Testing outside library packages is fine, but the class must also be top-level and instantiable by JUnit. If it extends ClassLoader, I wonder about the implications. It seems this could work, so I’ll define ClassPathScannerTest that extends ClassLoader and override methods to use this class within the tests. This approach might be unusual, but it could be a viable solution!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Questioning JUnit constructor compatibility**\\n\\nI’m wondering if JUnit can create a class with a public no-argument constructor when ClassLoader has a protected constructor. It seems like the implicit no-arg constructor would call super(), which should be fine since it’s accessible. While ClassLoader methods are final, getResources isn’t, which offers some flexibility. However, it looks like JUnit may not utilize the test class's classloader directly. I need to clarify how this affects my implementation in the tests.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring Java Constructors**\\n\\nI’m thinking about how implicit constructors work in Java. If a class is public and there's no explicit constructor, I believe the compiler creates a public no-argument constructor automatically. I wonder if the default constructor retains the same access level as the class itself. It seems like it calls a protected superclass constructor. Also, I should remember that in Java, I need to import classes without qualified names. Alright, I need to write that down!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_Z3FuprDgVdmGmsgpv7soILvD|fc_08f8acec3096d59c0169f7a9c8f5fc81969216fab52ce88862", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.flywaydb/flyway-core/11.14.1/src/test/java/com/ibm/flyway/ClassPathScannerTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage com.ibm.flyway;\n\nimport java.io.IOException;\nimport java.net.URL;\nimport java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets;\nimport java.nio.file.Files;\nimport java.nio.file.Path;\nimport java.util.Collection;\nimport java.util.Collections;\nimport java.util.Enumeration;\nimport java.util.List;\n\nimport org.flywaydb.core.api.Location;\nimport org.flywaydb.core.api.resource.LoadableResource;\nimport org.flywaydb.core.internal.scanner.ClasspathLocationHandler;\nimport org.flywaydb.core.internal.scanner.LocationScannerCache;\nimport org.flywaydb.core.internal.scanner.ResourceNameCache;\nimport org.flywaydb.core.internal.scanner.classpath.ClassPathScanner;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.io.TempDir;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\npublic class ClassPathScannerTest extends ClassLoader {\n\n    private static final String LOCATION_ROOT = \"db/migration\";\n    private static final String WEBSPHERE_LOCATION_MARKER = LOCATION_ROOT + \"/flyway.location\";\n\n    @TempDir\n    private Path temporaryDirectory;\n\n    private Path migrationDirectory;\n\n    @Test\n    void resolvesWebSphereClasspathLocationMarker() throws IOException {\n        migrationDirectory = Files.createDirectories(temporaryDirectory.resolve(LOCATION_ROOT));\n        Files.writeString(migrationDirectory.resolve(\"flyway.location\"), \"\");\n        Files.writeString(migrationDirectory.resolve(\"V1__create_table.sql\"), \"CREATE TABLE test(id INT);\");\n\n        ClassPathScanner<Object> scanner = new ClassPathScanner<>(\n                Object.class,\n                this,\n                StandardCharsets.UTF_8,\n                Location.fromPath(ClasspathLocationHandler.CLASSPATH_PREFIX, LOCATION_ROOT),\n                new ResourceNameCache(),\n                new LocationScannerCache(),\n                true,\n                false);\n\n        Collection<LoadableResource> resources = scanner.scanForResources();\n\n        assertThat(resources)\n                .extracting(LoadableResource::getAbsolutePath)\n                .contains(\"db/migration/V1__create_table.sql\");\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public Enumeration<URL> getResources(String name) throws IOException {\n        if (WEBSPHERE_LOCATION_MARKER.equals(name)) {\n            URL markerUrl = migrationDirectory.resolve(\"flyway.location\").toUri().toURL();\n            return Collections.enumeration(List.of(markerUrl));\n        }\n        return super.getResources(name);\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 800, "output": 1761, "cacheRead": 24064, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 26625, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777838518813, "responseId": "resp_08f8acec3096d59c0169f7a9b7469c819693ba4bb6768901ff"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_Z3FuprDgVdmGmsgpv7soILvD|fc_08f8acec3096d59c0169f7a9c8f5fc81969216fab52ce88862", "toolName": "write", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully wrote 2639 bytes to tests/src/org.flywaydb/flyway-core/11.14.1/src/test/java/com/ibm/flyway/ClassPathScannerTest.java"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1777838538817}]}
